caption: Great food and ambience, food is super nice, must try
Great food!

I loved the atmosphere and the wait staff was great. It was my first time at a restaurant in months. I gave it four stars because I was not entirely jazzed about the food...it wasn't bad, just didn't wow me. I wish there was quite a bit more egg as that was the meat for my entree.
One of the best Drunken Noodle dishes in the Boston area (and I've tried almost all of them). I asked for 'extra spicy,' which had a good kick. Service was really fast, too.
I said no onions.  The lettuce they gave customers — when you ordered chicken lettuce wrap.
I adore this place a lot. there is a very nice air. The food is splendid. the service is effective and the stuff is professional. The cost is satisfactory. I highly recommend.

Ordered To-Go one night after going through all the reviews and thought of giving a try. Food did looked good But to my disappointment all of the chicken smelled like I was in poultry farm surrounded by chicken. This just ruined my appetite.

Website needs work. I tried to order online for today, the receipt came through saying it was for delivery in a week from now. I called up to change or cancel and they said they cannot.  When I've eaten here in person pre-covid it was great.
Great service and good food !
Too salty and the portion sizes are small for low quality ingredients.

I often take my friends to this restaurant with my highest recommendations. I  go to this restaurant often. I get very good feedback from my friends. The the food there is fantastic and the crew is efficient and cooperative. Whenever we visit this place we enjoy a splendid evening.  I warmly recommend this restaurant.
Food was really good. They have good vegetarian alternative. And their Thai basil fried rice has good taste and quantities.

My Moo Krob Kra Paw was amazing!  I do love the flavor of basil and the crispy pork! It comes with rice separately, which was very nice of them to do this. I picked up last Sunday, planned to have it at home but ended up at the park nearby. :D It's so good that I cannot wait to get back home (and it won't be as this crispy -- best to have it asap).  Friendly people here. Parking can be challenging but this place worth visiting and 3 rounds of finding a parking spot!  Highly recommended.

THEY ARE NOT OPEN DO NOT ORDER FROM THEM.  Saw they were open on Google, ordered food but it never came. Tried calling their number, but no one answered.  They should update their service hours and availability.

10 stars for the food! Big portions, GREAT taste, very reasonable prices. I always eat here at least once anytime I'm in the area. 2 things to be aware of though. Very steep narrow down staircase to enter. Second, the wait staff tends to take awhile for everything (from drinks, to taking your order, to bringing the check).

Ha! So I found another good Thai restaurant in Cambridge! Good service, good atmosphere, and good Thai food.  I suggest to ask for fish sauce and chilies, which it will come as the condiment jars. So you can add vinegar, fish sauce, and chilies to your fried rice or noodles.  Thai beer is cheap here.  10% discount with student ID.  ส้มตำปลาร้าแซ่บอยู่ (papaya salad with pickled fish is cool.) But non-Thai people may find it difficult to understand why many Thai ladies love this dish.
This spot is worth visiting. They serve large portions for convenient prices. Constantly well organized and with fantastic mood. Will come back again.
The customer service is regularly swift, excellent vibes, nice staff members. I will return again when I get in the area.

I get to eat here a lot since I work right next to it. I got to say their customer service is always good and they keep the place neat constantly. Pricing is reasonable and they serve generous portions.

(Translated by Google) Great place to dine in a good setting: very clean, excellent service, good food. The chef even took into account the fact that I do not like a too spicy dish. Wonderful!  (Original) Отличное место для того чтобы пообедать в хорошей обстановке: очень чисто,отличное обслуживание,хорошая кухня. Шеф учел даже то,что я не люблю слишком острое блюдо. Замечательно!
Decent Thai food in Cambridge. They have student discount and prices are relatively good without it too.

Great place for Thai food around Harvard Square. Been here a few times, will go back again. Love the lunch box specials as well as the other dishes. Safe recommendation - I am not an expert in Thai food, so cannot say how authentic it is. But I love flavorful and spicy food and love this place.

Located in a basement level, the restaurant itself has two separate dining areas. It has all typical Thai restaurant's menu. We ordered some appetizers, two different soups and entries. Our food came fast, everything that we ordered was tasty and fresh. Service was fast and pleasant.
FIREEEEEE, pad Thai, golden bags, scallion pancakes, mango rice. All great and quick service.
Good and delicious. Tom yum was a little sweat but it is ok.
Delicious food! You may not think is much from the outside but once you go downstairs is very cozy and inviting!
Down the stairs to a basement delight! Thai  cuisine at it's best! Enjoy!
Amazing food ... Clean kitchen ... Really good price.
Good Thai food! Had the drunken noodle and it was worth the price :)
This place has such delicious yummy food and a very good service. Will go there again :)
Very delicious food, nice environment

This place is delicious. I forgot to take a picture of the money bags that I love to order, cause I just dove right in without taking a picture 😅 I ordered chicken drunken noodle and it was great! Not too spicy but has a little kick. The shrimp papaya salad was okay. It only came with 2 shrimps!! Only 2!! But otherwise would highly recommend!! Try this place out if you like Thai food!!
Affordable price good food nice people
delicious thai curry!
I liked their Tai I iced tea
Huge fan: good food, great atmosphere, and the BEST thai iced tea
Best Thai food in Cambridge
Neat little Thai restaurant near Harvard Square. Good food. Good service

Ridiculously bad service! This guy just throw the check at our desk and yelled at us at the end!

Average Thai food compared to their other location in the area (Spice, which I love)! I ordered one of their curries and the egg noodles actually seem like noodles from a ramen packet. Overall, looking around it seems like Thai food produced for the masses.
Literally the best Thai food in the East Coast, very yummy pad thai!

I came here with my friend today for a weekday lunch. He comes all the time and always gets the shrimp pad see ew. I hadn't been here in several years and decided to get the seafood lemongrass soup noodle ($13.95).  The taste of the soup and noodles were good, but the quantity of noodles was a bit skimpy. It was less than a small bowl of pho at Le's. There were two shrimps, two scallops, and two pieces of squid.  The interiors are a bit crowded, and the service is subpar. They tried to take my friend's plate away three times before he finished.
(Translated by Google) Good service, great value for money and relaxed atmosphere.  (Original) Bom atendimento, ótimo custo-benefício e ambiente descontraído.
Excellent, attentive service.
nice thai joint in Harvard square. Love their salmon chochee and Tom Yum soup. Their is   gelato parlour and bubble tea cafe next door for dessert
We got in there accidentally thinking it is a bubble tea place. Ended up ordering couple items which were good and reasonable in price. One portion of curries could even good enough for two peoole

I wish I had better things to say about 9 Tastes.  The service was courteous and efficient, but the food was really subpar.  The spring rolls were mediocre, though properly crispy; the real problem was the main dish, vegetables and tofu in tamarind sauce.  The tofu was on the cold side and squish in a way even tofu shouldn't be. The vegetables were overcooked and appeared to come from a can. And the sauce was cloying.  They may do better with non-vegetarian dishes; I hope so.

Delicious! One of my favorite restaurants in the square!

Higher end of Thai restaurants, great service and atmosphere. I wasn’t blown away by the food but some dishes are solid compared to other top Thai restaurants in town.

Went with a large party so i was able to try many dishes. All were tasty. None were exceptionally good or bad.   It is popular enough to need and take reservations, so that is a big plus!  I will visit again.

True Thai dishes with good amount of zing, when it should be there (green curry, for example). Tofu is deliciously fried, so it absorbs all the flavor of whatever it comes with. Yum! Service is relatively fast, which is great if you are going to a show at the ART after.

Food was just okay Yelp gave it 4 stars I give it 3. Not sure if Boston is known for Thai food but I've definitely had better Thai food in different cities. The service was great it's in a basement so it's a little damp smelling if that bothers you.

Horrible, unfriendly and poor quality food!!Unfriendly staff and poor quality food, and please tell the cook when he's been to the toilet for 5 min to close the door behind him....

Terrible experience! The dinner was a scam from start to finish. The owner and her staff are clearly motivated by money and couldn't care less if the customer enjoys his food or not. The food looks like it was microwaved (Trust me: I know microwaved food when I see it--> hot at the edges and  stone cold at its center) and does not taste fresh (The meat was chewy and had a rotten taste). The service and the decoration are even worst than the food. For instance, the waiter does not even welcome you when he has clearly heard you say hello to him, and he does not even bother to look away when you're attempting to type in your credit card's code in the machine. This place was absolutely disgusting and I wouldn't recommend it to my worst enemy!

This place satisfies the "decent thai food" urge you can get sometimes. The food isn't spectacular, but like other asian places, they aren't afraid to make your food flavorful. They are also pretty good with letting people stay for meetings and such, as I sometimes go with others that I plan to have longer conversations with.

Eaten here several times - the prices are reasonable, portions are large, and there are many options. The food is usually of decent quality, and I prefer it to the nearby Spice. Though it can get busy and loud, service times are usually quite fast.
Solid Thai, middle of the road

Came here for dinner.  Food: Honey glazed duck - Was okay. It wasn't up to par with the price of the dish. $19?  Grilled chicken with papaya salad - This was a combo dish. Forgot the official menu name.  The papaya salad had a strong fish taste. Definitely not a fan.  The chicken was good.  Service was good.  They were prompt and friendly.  Maybe I ordered the wrong things hopefully you can try the other dishes.
Delicious food! Specially their curry! The place is really nice inside too! Love their food!
Had a nice lunch here. Not pricey and the services were good. Foods I had were a bit sweet, but they are typical Thai foods (of course, spicy is also typical).
The taste of fried rice are good, but the rices are so strong today
Must go must see must eat the food was amazing
Same owners as Spice up the street and the food tastes similar as well. The ambiance isn't as nice as Spice though because it's in a basement but a good alternative when Spice is packed.
OK Thai place in Harvard Square. Nothing exceptional...
Good Thai food.  Only complaint is that it doesn't take Amex, but I'm not taking a star off
Great mango friend rice.

"It's Okay" perfectly describes this place. Both times I've been here, I have had the same overall feeling of it's okay. The food is so so, although the happy hour 1/2 price spring rolls are actually pretty good. The service is also very so-so. The ambiance is severely lacking. The major upside is the location...right in the heart of Harvard Square, and one of (if not the) only Thai places.
Some wonderful dishes, but not much to recommend it besides to gain variety in Harvard square

Hidden treasure in Harvard Square! Ever since discovering this place, I've been coming back twice a month. I would recommend the pumpkin curry or avocado curry. The chef can make your order customized to your tastes, so if you enjoy very spicy dishes, he/she can accommodate.

The portions at 9 Tastes are rather small for the prices that you pay.  I had the basil fried rice, which I didn't think was very flavorful.  Even so, if the portions were larger, I would bump this to four stars.  Currently, the value to price ratio is too low to return.
Seafood fried rice is good!

The food here may not be the best Thai food you'll ever eat, but for the price and the location, it's certainly up there for me. Drunken noodles are very good, as is pad thai. Thai iced coffee was also quite good. The downstairs atmosphere makes it kind of fun and interesting, too; feels like a hole in the wall, but isn't divy like that can be sometimes.
Good thai food. Thai ice tea is good

Very cheap, flavorful Thai food with fast and efficient service (they have never gotten an order wrong!) The menus have a large selection of food but it does not stray away from quality. They have lots of specials and vegetarian friendly.

First food I've had in Cambridge that was actually spicy, and I've tried quite a few Indian meals in the area.  I had an avocado curry which was an unusual choice, but worked really well and was super tasty.  The staff were attentive and lovely.  They had a decent beer selection too.

9 Tastes Thai Cuisine excels in two things: first, their special "9 Tastes Pad Thai" is the best version of the famous Thai dish in the entire area. They use chicken, shrimp, and vegetables to which they add their home-made special sauce of which I'm a big fan. Other dishes are great too, including basil fried rice and red curry. Second, their service is extremely fast - both for sit-down meals and take-out. For the best value I recommend take-out since that's the fastest route to their delicious Pad Thai. Definitely worth visiting!
not the best Thai food, the ingrediens are not as fresh either. Overal not bad, but definitely not worth my money.

This is a place close to my heart. My brother lives in El Salvador and whenever he comes to home to Boston he always asks to eat Thai food. The first time he came home we wandered around Harvard square looking for a place. We asked some nice florists where the best thai was around. They pointed us to 9 tastes. I'm so happy they did, we go back constantly. It's my go to place for sit-down thai and their drunken noodle is amazing, noah loves the pad thai - and they are sensitive to his nut allergy so that's good! No death! Spicy, lots of colorful veggies (they even spring for red peppers! Novel idea!) and seriously good value. Lunch specials are something that makes my heart skip.

This is my favorite Thai restaurant in Cambridge- hands down!!  It's not fancy but the food is wonderful. I always get the Pad Thai, either the 9 Tastes, Chicken and Shrimp, or crispy. The service is pretty fast. They also have wine and beer. There are normally lots of students so it's not the quietest place, but again the food is wonderful!
Our favorite thai food around Cambridge. Drunken noodles and the 9 tastes pad thai are our favorites. On the down side, the place can be pretty loud and crowded, but the service it usually fast.
fantastic thai with great service. a great deal in harvard square without any of the pretention or fake pizzazz. simply good food at a great price.
